#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.156"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.156:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.156:0.2"
msgid "16. Saddhammavagga "
msgstr "16. The True Teaching "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.156:0.3"
msgid "156. Tatiyasaddhammasammosasutta "
msgstr "156. The Decline of the True Teaching (3rd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an5.156:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattanti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these five things lead to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching. "

msgctxt "an5.156:1.2"
msgid "Katame pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.156:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhū duggahitaṃ suttantaṃ pariyāpuṇanti dunnikkhittehi padabyañjanehi. "
msgstr "It’s when the mendicants memorize discourses that they learned incorrectly, with misplaced words and phrases. "

msgctxt "an5.156:1.4"
msgid "Dunnikkhittassa, bhikkhave, padabyañjanassa atthopi dunnayo hoti. "
msgstr "When the words and phrases are misplaced, the meaning is misinterpreted. "

msgctxt "an5.156:1.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "This is the first thing that leads to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an5.156:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhū dubbacā honti, dovacassakaraṇehi dhammehi samannāgatā, akkhamā appadakkhiṇaggāhino anusāsaniṃ. "
msgstr "Furthermore, the mendicants are hard to admonish, having qualities that make them hard to admonish. They’re impatient, and don’t take instruction respectfully. "

msgctxt "an5.156:2.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "This is the second thing … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.179, sc3
msgctxt "an5.156:3.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ye te bhikkhū bahussutā āgatāgamā dhammadharā vinayadharā mātikādharā, te na sakkaccaṃ suttantaṃ paraṃ vācenti; "
msgstr "Furthermore, the mendicants who are very learned—knowledgeable in the scriptures, who have memorized the teachings, the texts on monastic training, and the outlines—don’t carefully make others recite the discourses. "

msgctxt "an5.156:3.2"
msgid "tesaṃ accayena chinnamūlako suttanto hoti appaṭisaraṇo. "
msgstr "When they pass away, the discourses are cut off at the root, with no-one to preserve them. "

msgctxt "an5.156:3.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "This is the third thing … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an5.156:4.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, therā bhikkhū bāhulikā honti sāthalikā okkamane pubbaṅgamā paviveke nikkhittadhurā, na vīriyaṃ ārabhanti appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya. "
msgstr "Furthermore, the senior mendicants are indulgent and slack, leaders in backsliding, neglecting seclusion, not rousing energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized. "

msgctxt "an5.156:4.2"
msgid "Tesaṃ pacchimā janatā diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjati. "
msgstr "Those who come after them follow their example. "

msgctxt "an5.156:4.3"
msgid "Sāpi hoti bāhulikā sāthalikā okkamane pubbaṅgamā paviveke nikkhittadhurā, na vīriyaṃ ārabhati appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya. "
msgstr "They too are indulgent and slack … "

msgctxt "an5.156:4.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "This is the fourth thing … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an5.156:5.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃgho bhinno hoti. "
msgstr "Furthermore, there’s a schism in the Saṅgha. "

#. VAR: pariccajanā → pariccajā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an5.156:5.2"
msgid "Saṃghe kho pana, bhikkhave, bhinne aññamaññaṃ akkosā ca honti, aññamaññaṃ paribhāsā ca honti, aññamaññaṃ parikkhepā ca honti, aññamaññaṃ pariccajanā ca honti. "
msgstr "When the Saṅgha is split, they abuse, insult, block, and reject each other. "

msgctxt "an5.156:5.3"
msgid "Tattha appasannā ceva nappasīdanti, pasannānañca ekaccānaṃ aññathattaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "This doesn’t inspire confidence in those without it, and it causes some with confidence to change their minds. "

msgctxt "an5.156:5.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "This is the fifth thing that leads to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.156:5.5"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattanti. "
msgstr "These five things lead to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an5.156:6.1"
msgid "Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattanti. "
msgstr "These five things lead to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching. "

msgctxt "an5.156:6.2"
msgid "Katame pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an5.156:6.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhū suggahitaṃ suttantaṃ pariyāpuṇanti sunikkhittehi padabyañjanehi. "
msgstr "It’s when the mendicants memorize discourses that have been learned correctly, with well placed words and phrases. "

msgctxt "an5.156:6.4"
msgid "Sunikkhittassa, bhikkhave, padabyañjanassa atthopi sunayo hoti. "
msgstr "When the words and phrases are well organized, the meaning is correctly interpreted. "

msgctxt "an5.156:6.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "This is the first thing that leads to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.180, sc7
msgctxt "an5.156:7.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhū suvacā honti sovacassakaraṇehi dhammehi samannāgatā, khamā padakkhiṇaggāhino anusāsaniṃ. "
msgstr "Furthermore, the mendicants are easy to admonish, having qualities that make them easy to admonish. They’re patient, and take instruction respectfully. "

msgctxt "an5.156:7.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "This is the second thing … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an5.156:8.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ye te bhikkhū bahussutā āgatāgamā dhammadharā vinayadharā mātikādharā, te sakkaccaṃ suttantaṃ paraṃ vācenti; "
msgstr "Furthermore, the mendicants who are very learned—knowledgeable in the scriptures, who have memorized the teachings, the texts on monastic training, and the outlines—carefully make others recite the discourses. "

#. VAR: na chinnamūlako → acchinnamūlako (mr)
msgctxt "an5.156:8.2"
msgid "tesaṃ accayena na chinnamūlako suttanto hoti sappaṭisaraṇo. "
msgstr "When they pass away, the discourses aren’t cut off at the root, and they have someone to preserve them. "

msgctxt "an5.156:8.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "This is the third thing … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an5.156:9.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, therā bhikkhū na bāhulikā honti na sāthalikā, okkamane nikkhittadhurā paviveke pubbaṅgamā; vīriyaṃ ārabhanti appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya. "
msgstr "Furthermore, the senior mendicants are not indulgent and slack, leaders in backsliding, neglecting seclusion. They rouse energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized. "

msgctxt "an5.156:9.2"
msgid "Tesaṃ pacchimā janatā diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjati. "
msgstr "Those who come after them follow their example. "

msgctxt "an5.156:9.3"
msgid "Sāpi hoti na bāhulikā na sāthalikā, okkamane nikkhittadhurā paviveke pubbaṅgamā, vīriyaṃ ārabhati appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya. "
msgstr "They too are not indulgent or slack … "

msgctxt "an5.156:9.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "This is the fourth thing … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an5.156:10.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, saṅgho samaggo sammodamāno avivadamāno ekuddeso phāsuṃ viharati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, the Saṅgha lives comfortably, in harmony, appreciating each other, without quarreling, with one recitation. "

msgctxt "an5.156:10.2"
msgid "Saṅghe kho pana, bhikkhave, samagge na ceva aññamaññaṃ akkosā honti, na ca aññamaññaṃ paribhāsā honti, na ca aññamaññaṃ parikkhepā honti, na ca aññamaññaṃ pariccajanā honti. "
msgstr "When the Saṅgha is in harmony, they don’t abuse, insult, block, or reject each other. "

msgctxt "an5.156:10.3"
msgid "Tattha appasannā ceva pasīdanti, pasannānañca bhiyyobhāvo hoti. "
msgstr "This inspires confidence in those without it, and increases confidence in those who have it. "

msgctxt "an5.156:10.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "This is the fifth thing that leads to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.156:10.5"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattantī”ti. "
msgstr "These five things lead to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.156:10.6"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

